in_val = float('inf')\n            min_col = -1\n            for j in range(n):\n                if dp[i-1][j] < min_val:\n                    second_min_val = min_val\n                    min_val = dp[i-1][j]\n                    min_col = j\n                elif dp[i-1][j] < second_min_val:\n                    second_min_val = dp[i-1][j]\n            \n            # Update the DP table for the current row\n            for j in range(n):\n                if j == min_col:\n                    dp[i][j] += second_min_val\n                else:\n                    dp[i][j] += min_val\n        \n        # The answer is the minimum value in the last row of the DP table\n        return min(dp[-1])\n```\n\nThis solution uses dynamic programming to keep track of the minimum falling path sum with non-zero shifts. It iterates through each row, updating the current cell with the sum of the current cell and the minimum value from the previous row, ensuring that no two elements chosen in adjacent rows are in the same column. If the smallest value in the previous row is in the same column, it uses the second smallest value instead.", "estimated_date": 1575763200000}